Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development and optimization of Cellular-Vehicle-to-Everything (CV2X) communication, which is a type of wireless networking technology.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the need for simulations to test and optimize algorithms and procedures prior to implementation, which involves information processing and transmission.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of a system-level simulator for CV2X communication, which involves control and management of the system.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is possible as the paper briefly mentions the need for high-level reliability in CV2X communication, which may involve security measures.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of network-assisted communication for cooperative driving, which may involve AI techniques.
